	<annotations>
		<text id="0" type="text/plain" rect="(376.9855072463768, 75.8840579710145, 150.0, 56.0)" font-family="Segoe UI" font-size="16">machine learning
</text>
		<text id="1" type="text/plain" rect="(1767.9166666666674, 121.25000000000023, 443.33333333333303, 166.0)" font-family="Segoe UI" font-size="16">Model Comparison --
Based on the model and data, Random Forest gave the best R2 Value

It has the least RMSE score (0.107) and highest R2 score (0.799) --&gt; with a margin of 0.10 difference from kNN and Linear Regression</text>
		<text id="2" type="text/plain" rect="(2517.083333333333, 197.49999999999966, 348.3333333333335, 232.0)" font-family="Segoe UI" font-size="16">Feature Importance
median_income: median income for households within a block of houses
housing_median_age: median age of a house within a block (the newer the bulding the lower number)
total_bedrooms: total number of bedrooms within a block

</text>
		<text id="3" type="text/plain" rect="(2830.0, 1137.5, 150.0, 29.0)" font-family="Segoe UI" font-size="16" />
